# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) to override the e2e database used by
# `pnpm test:e2e`. If this variable is unset, the script boots a throwaway
# postgres:16 container via Docker and tears it down on exit.
#
# Hosted Supabase WILL NOT WORK — the e2e suites CREATE/DROP roles
# (`app_user`, `app_system`) and the hosted `postgres` user lacks the
# necessary privileges. Use one of:
#   - local Docker postgres (the default, no `.env` needed)
#   - local Supabase (`supabase start` -> port 54322)
#   - any other reachable Postgres where you can CREATE ROLE
#
# Examples:
# GUARDDOG_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@127.0.0.1:54322/postgres
# GUARDDOG_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://guarddog:guarddog@127.0.0.1:5432/guarddog_e2e
